description.p:
HPLC analysis of the compounds shows a sharp, single peak using various optimized HPLC conditions, including:
1) C18 column, ACN/H2O 50/50 to 100% ACN 10 min, 2 min 100% ACNH, 230 nm, 1.5 ml/min, 30° C., 16 min;
2) Synergy column, MeOH/H2O 75/25 to 100% MeOH 10 min, 2 min 100% MeOH, 230 nm, 1.5 ml/min, 30° C., 15 min;
3) Synergy column, ACN/H2O 50/50 3 min, 80-100% ACN/H2O 10 min, 2 min 100% ACN, 230 nm, 1.5 ml/min, 30° C., 15 min;
4) Synergy column, 70-100% ACN/H2O 10 min, 100% ACN 2 min, 230 nm, 1.5 ml/min, 30° C., 15 min;
5) C18 column, MeOH/H2O 95/5 to 100% MeOH 10 min, 2 min 100% MeOH, 230 nm, 1.5 ml/min, 30° C., 16 min; and
6) Synergy column, ACN/H2O 80/20 10 min, 100% ACN 2 min, 230 nm, 1.5 ml/min, 30° C., 15 min.
